Patch Set 4: Code-Review-2

I really think we should approve the spec first: https://review.opendev.org/#/c/656895/

Patch Set 4:

I think this looks good, and nice work porting the tests over from Cinder.

The current tests ensure that we're getting the correct behavior with respect to key deletion in Barbican.  We should also have tests to make sure that this new codepath in the image-delete call doesn't introduce any anomalous behaviors into the image deletion process.  In other words, we need to make sure that the error conditions outlined in the spec are being handled correctly:
https://review.opendev.org/#/c/656895/4/specs/train/approved/glance/barbican-secret-deletion-support.rst@99

Patch Set 4: -Code-Review

Spec has merged.  I'd still like to see more tests, but they could be done in a follow-up patch.
